headline: Weighing Weebit Nano’s Valuation After The Texas Instruments Deal And New 2026 Revenue Guidance
summary: What the Texas Instruments deal and new guidance mean for Weebit Nano Weebit Nano (ASX:WBT) has drawn fresh attention after licensing its ReRAM technology to Texas Instruments and issuing minimum revenue guidance of A$10 million for fiscal 2026, marking a clear operational milestone. See our latest analysis for Weebit Nano. After the Texas Instruments announcement and new 2026 revenue guidance, interest has picked up. headline: 2 Cash-Producing Stocks with Impressive Fundamentals and 1 We Brush Off
summary: While strong cash flow is a key indicator of stability, it doesn’t always translate to superior returns. Some cash-heavy businesses struggle with inefficient spending, slowing demand, or weak competitive positioning.
